China is negotiating with Pakistan tobuy 5,000 tonnes of cotton this year, after importing the sameamount last year under a barter agreement, Chinese consulatesources said.    Chinese ambassador Tian Ding told a meeting of Pakistaniindustrialists on Thursday that China intended to increaseimports from Pakistan to reduce a trade imbalance.    Pakistani officials estimate the country's cotton outputfrom the current crop at a record 7.6 mln bales (375 poundseach). Last year's output totalled 7.2 mln bales and domesticconsumption was just below three mln bales, they said. REUTER&#3;